# IDK Digital Solutions — Git Line Ending Rules
#
# WHY THIS FILE EXISTS:
#   On Windows, Git defaults to converting LF → CRLF on checkout and CRLF → LF
#   on commit (core.autocrlf=true). This causes "LF will be replaced by CRLF"
#   warnings on every git add and creates noise in diffs.
#
#   More importantly, shell scripts (.sh) and certain config files MUST use LF
#   line endings — CRLF breaks bash execution with "bad interpreter" errors.
#
#   This file overrides the per-machine Git config and enforces consistent
#   line endings for the whole team, regardless of OS.
#
# RULES:
#   text=auto   — Git decides; normalises to LF in the repo, converts to OS
#                 line ending on checkout (safe default for most files)
#   eol=lf      — Always LF, everywhere (shell scripts, Terraform, Python)
#   eol=crlf    — Always CRLF (Windows-only files, rare)
#   binary      — No conversion at all (images, compiled files)

# ── Default: normalise all text files to LF in the repo ──────────────────────
* text=auto eol=lf

# ── Shell scripts — must always be LF or bash will refuse to run them ─────────
*.sh    text eol=lf

# ── Terraform ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.tf        text eol=lf
*.tfvars    text eol=lf
*.hcl       text eol=lf

# ── Python ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.py    text eol=lf

# ── Markdown and docs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.md    text eol=lf

# ── Config and data files ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.json      text eol=lf
*.yaml      text eol=lf
*.yml       text eol=lf
*.toml      text eol=lf
*.txt       text eol=lf
*.env       text eol=lf
*.gitignore text eol=lf

# ── Binary files — no conversion ──────────────────────────────────────────────
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.gif   binary
*.ico   binary
*.zip   binary
*.tar   binary
*.gz    binary
*.pem   binary
*.p12   binary
